    <prj:ScienceGoal>
        <prj:name>Minding the gap in the GW Ori disk</prj:name>
        <prj:note>We aim to determine whether the bright circumsystem disk in the GW Ori system is, indeed, a circum-triple disk. We will observe the disk at high angular resolution in both Band 7 (345 GHz) continuum and CO and 13CO(J=3-2) line emission. Through both image-plane and uv-plane analysis, we will determine whether there is a cavity carved by a third stellar component. In so doing, we will test the hypothesis that the emission indeed derives from a circum-triple disk, akin to those observed around some pre-main sequence binary systeme.
</prj:note>
